title: Artemis 1 launch boosts ESA’s exploration ambitions
summary: The successful launch of the Artemis 1 mission comes just in time for the European Space Agency as it seeks support from its member states for new exploration initiatives.

title: Space Force opens door to Blue Origin with new cooperative agreement
summary: The U.S. Space Systems Command signed an agreement with Blue Origin that “paves the way” for the company’s New Glenn rocket to compete for national security launch contracts

title: SpaceX to launch last new cargo Dragon spacecraft
summary: A SpaceX Dragon launching soon to the International Space Station is the last cargo version of the spacecraft the company expects to build, with one more crewed spacecraft under construction.

title: Orion ready for lunar flyby maneuver
summary: NASA has approved plans to proceed with the next critical milestone in the Artemis 1 mission, a maneuver by the uncrewed Orion spacecraft as it flies by the moon Nov. 21.

title: White House, Congress praise long-delayed first SLS launch
summary: The inaugural flight of the Space Launch System won positive reactions from the White House and Congress, celebrating the successful liftoff while overlooking the vehicle’s extensive delays.
